properties.areaDesc: San Luis Obispo County Central Coast; Santa Barbara County Central Coast
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 3 at 9:34PM PST until January 6 at 3:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Large breaking waves of 8 to 12 feet with local sets to
14 feet. Dangerous rip currents are likely.

* WHERE...Beaches along the Central Coast.

* WHEN...From 7 PM Saturday to 3 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...There is an increased risk for ocean drowning. Rip
currents can pull swimmers and surfers out to sea. Large
breaking waves can cause injury, wash people off beaches and
rocks, and capsize small boats near shore.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The highest surf is expected to occur along
west and northwest facing shores.
properties.instruction:
Remain out of the water due to dangerous surf conditions, or stay
near occupied lifeguard towers. Rock jetties can be deadly in
such conditions, stay off the rocks.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM SATURDAY TO 3 AM PST MONDAY
